This MVEBU target is intended to be used on devices based on Marvell ArmadaXP/Armada37x/Armada38x ARM-compatible CPUs (aka PJ4x/PJ5x).

Following instruction were tested on Globalscape Mirabox v1.0 but should be applyable to other devices with NAND support.
Kernel resides in second NAND partition /dev/mtd1 (4MB) using uImage format.
Root filesystem resides third partition /dev/mtd2 (1016MB) using UBIFS.

Currently only manual install/re-install procedure tested.
For initial system flash, use combined "factory" (kernel+rootfs) image: openwrt-mvebu-armada-370-mirabox-squashfs-factory.img.
(If your factory image is greater than 32MB, please update 'image_size' accordingly)

The following commands should be invoked from boot loader (uBoot) prompt.
1. Setup tftp server with root at /home/tmp.
2. Copy factory image to tftp server root.
3. Prepare uBoot environment (modify network paramters if needed):
	resetenv; reset
	mainlineLinux yes; save; reset
	setenv console 'console=ttyS0,115200 panic=30'; setenv bootargs_root 'ubi.mtd=2'
	setenv ipaddr '192.168.1.200'; setenv serverip '192.168.1.14'; setenv rootpath '/home/tmp/'
	setenv loadaddr '0x2000000'; setenv loadsize '0x400000'
	setenv rootaddr '0x400000'; setenv rootsize '0x3fc00000'
	setenv imagesize '0x2000000'; setenv imagename 'openwrt-mvebu-armada-370-mirabox-squashfs-factory.img'
	setenv clean_mem 'mw ${loadaddr} ${imagesize}'
	setenv fetch_image 'tftpboot ${loadaddr} ${rootpath}${imagename}'
	setenv write_image 'nand erase ${rootaddr} ${rootsize}; nand write.e ${loadaddr} ${rootaddr} ${imagesize}'
	setenv read_boot 'nand read.e ${loadaddr} ${rootaddr} ${loadsize}'
	setenv flash_image 'run clean_mem; run fetch_image; run write_image'
	setenv bootcmd 'run clean_mem; run read_boot; setenv bootargs ${console} ${bootargs_root}; bootm ${loadaddr}'
	save
3. Install openwrt:
	run flash_image
4. Boot into openwrt:
	boot

Good luck
